436 /* basic concepts at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queue_(abstract_data_type)
437 * our high-performance queue uses double-buffered fixed memory arrays
438 * it does NOT use dynamically linked lists to reduce ptr overhead
439 * if overflow occurs it either overwrites oldest data or resizes the queue
440 * this depends on the 'resize' flag, if true then overflow will only occur
441 * when memory is capped by the apps total allocatable RAM.
442 * npRealloc() is called to resize, it uses runtime optimized memory pools
443 * in certain cases there is no data copy cost as the memory pool
444 * may already be configured with additional free space at end of the array
445 * A & B buffers are sequentially re-allocated over two program synce cycles
446 * avoids data copy by syncing the resize to the AB swap when the que is clear
447 */
